mint and, per mutation B, makes the node-failure tests STRONGER, not decorative). Every stimulus is legitimate: node failure is provoked by a DELETED Node (apierrors NotFound / absent object / removal from state.Nodes), never by a cordon — the R21 trap is avoided. Net: no test asserts the bug and no fixture asserts an illegal end-state. The single observation worth surfacing is a defense-in-depth gap: the isolated unit tests that call c.applyResolution directly bypass the invariant oracle, because applyResolution is not one of the three entry points (Reconcile/ActivateReservations/HandleNodeFailure) that install the deferred check — so those tests rely solely on their own assertions (which are load-bearing, per mutation F). The production path and the quiescence integration cover applyResolution via ActivateReservations, so this is low severity.",
